<paragraph xmlns:gate="http://www.gate.ac.uk" gate:gateId="0" gate:annotMaxId="239">Abendroth, Hermann, conductor and pedagogue; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="237" RE="Jan. 19, 1883" Pred="birth" Pred-tyoe="time"><Birth gate:gateId="233" predict="birth">b.</Birth> <Location gate:gateId="186" rule1="Location1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Frankfurt</Location>, <Date gate:gateId="187" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">Jan. 19, 1883</Date></Event_Birth>; <Event_Birth gate:gateId="238" RE="May 29, 1956" Pred="death" Pred-tyoe="time"><Death gate:gateId="234" predict="death">d.</Death> Jena, <Date gate:gateId="189" rule1="DateNameRev" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">May 29, 1956</Date></Event_Birth>. He studied in <Location gate:gateId="190" rule1="InLoc1" locType="city" rule2="LocFinal">Munich</Location> (190011); Essen (<Date gate:gateId="191" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1911</Date>also conducted at the Berlin State Opera (<Date gate:gateId="193" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1923</Date>the Leipzig Cons, and conductor of the Gewandhaus Concerts. In <Date gate:gateId="195" rule1="TempYear3" kind="date" rule2="YearOnlyFinal">1947</Date> he was appointed director of the Musikhochschule in Weimar; in <Date gate:gateId="196" rule1="YearContext1" kind="date" rule2="DateOnlyFinal">1949</Date>, music director of the Leipzig Radio. </paragraph>